Sender  Belldandy~
Date    Wed May 24 19:38:41 2000~
Stamp   959215121
To      all~
Subject The `@RP`2bar``~
Text
There has been some confusion lately about what is allowed and not allowed
in the rp bar, and this news is to clear things up. 

Everyone is welcome in the rp bar at all times, provided they follow these
couple of rules.

1`#)`` If there is no rp session going on, then you are free to do whatever you
`7   ``you like in the bar until such time as a session starts up. At that time,
`7``   you must follow all of the following rules.

2`#)`` When there is an active rp session going on, you must either be actively
`7``   participating in the session, or be unobtrusive. The definition of
`7``   being obtrusive is as such: engaging in local disruptive behaviour. This
`7``   includes such things as OOC says, OOC emotes, OOC yells, OOC shouts and
`7``   spamming etc. However, you can be in the bar waiting, observing or for
`7``   whatever reason catches your fancy. Just `!don't be disruptive``!

3`#)`` If you are actively rping, and an something comes up OOC, then change your
`7``   communication channel. If you don't know if it is OOC or IC, then your
`7``   default behaviour should be to act as if it was OOC. Here  is a good
`7``   example:
`7``     You and three friends are going out to a movie later on tonight. You all
`7``     are rping, but you want to remind everyone what time to meet. Don't use
`7``     `^say`` to remind them, `@tell`` each one individually.  On the other hand, if
`7``     you and your three friends have a time set up to go and kick some
`7``     Satan-tucass, then that can be RPed, and is safe to `^say``. Just
`7``     remember if you don't know, use `@tell`` to communicate!

I hope this clears things up,
-`@B`2elldandy``
~
