Sender  Kyrn~
Date    Sat Nov 25 00:26:17 2000~
Stamp   975133577
To      all~
Subject AnimeMUD~
Text
After final deliberations with Vorlin, We have come to the conclusion that
port 5k will become port 9k .. aka AnimeMUD after final beta testing is
complete on that port. This is a public announcement that through Vorlin's
words, he will 'steer the ship' but I will always be the owner of AnimeMUD.
So here is what we are planning to do in the *NEAR* future.

A) All areas are currently being revamped under a building matrix I have
developed. The matrix is so extensive and will bring a whole new view of eq
here on the mud. Changes will be reflected when I finish all the areas
and I will post another news when they are implemented.
B) Autoquest eq will be revamped completely. Personally, I don't care for
the equipment that is implemented now. Vorlin and I are looking at a more
dynamic way to autoquest, aka. Smart Mobs who run from the hunter, and a bit
more extensive questing.. which even may take days. The autoquest equipment
will definately reimburse you for you extensive efforts, so i'm not trying
to short change anyone here.
C) Various little changes will take into effect: Better exp for grouping,
Quest Items becoming prized possessions, revamping of certain skills/spells,
introduction to various new clans for those pkillers, and overall attempt to
regain the mud atmosphere we *ALL* desire.

Here is what Vorlin and I would like to do. Because we both have the same
ideas on *how* the mud should run, we understand that certain changes will
affect players in a way that will force them to leave. This is *NOT* because
we are trying to filter any particular group of players; it's because there
will be some that are accustomed to AnimeMUD as it is now. I'm starting a slow
transition from 9k to 5k, but introducing new ideas and implementing them here.
Port 5k will follow with all changes which occur here. Meaning in the end, as
you, the players, become accustomed to the *new* way the mud is ran/developed/
implemented, and various code changes/eq changes/race changes/class changes, the
transition will not be a *system shock* to most here and Vorlin and I will be able
to retain those players, who in the end, are here for one reason: To have fun no
matter the changes. The changes might not be pretty on the outside..but if you take
a nonselfish look at the whole picture, you will realize that they were all
implemented to make the mud a better place. 8)

All I ask from you, the players, to just have enough support for Vorlin, for his hard
work he is putting into his port, and when the time comes, we will all see the long
hours he put in, to make this theme style mud, just a little bit better.

Kyrn, Bash-O-Matic
~
