Text
As many of you noticed (and were able to connect here), our connection has
been switched temporarily to the ISDN line.  Due to the speed difference,
I will be enforcing, along with the other IMMs, some rules to help keep
our bandwidth usage down.  Failure to follow these rules will lead to
the rest of the players being really mean to you.  And we'll probably
punish you, too.

1.  `&No Spamming.  You will be warned if we see it, and punished if
`&we repeatedly see it.``
2.  `&No idling.  If you are going to be on-line, play.  If not, quit.`7
`&This is true for autoquesting as well.  Do other things if you are`7
`&autoquesting, not just sit there and wait for the next autoquest.``
`&Role-Playing IS doing something.  This would be thing to help pass`7
`&that time.``
3.  `&Keep it quiet about lag.  We already know it's laggy.
`&Just be happy we're still up.`7


Batanen Fujioka
~
